					<h4>Literary Odds & Ends</h4>
		
		<h1>Western Literary Roundup</h1>
		<h2><i></i></h2>
		<div class="text-feature_print">
							<p>By Jenny Shank, 5-18-07</p>
			
			
							<p>It&#8217;s nearly summertime and the weather is fine, so regional authors are hitting the road for readings and conferences.
</p>
<p>
Wyoming writer Michael Shay recently emailed about the annual Wyoming Writers, Inc. conference to be held at Hot Springs State Park in Thermopolis on June 1 and 2.&nbsp; Writers to be featured include &#8220;Mike and Kathy Gear, historical fiction and mystery writers from Thermopolis; Tim Sandlin, novelist from Jackson; Sandra Alcosser, Montana&#8217;s poet laureate; editor John Helfers; and children&#8217;s author Dr. Toran Isom.&#8221; More details are on <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hummingbirdminds.com/" title="Shay&#8217;s website">Shay&#8217;s website</a>.
</p>
<p>
Montana author John Clayton wrote in about his tour for new nonfiction book, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.johnclaytonbooks.com/thecowboygirl.htm" title=""The Cowboy Girl: The Life of Caroline Lockhart.&#8221;">&#8220;The Cowboy Girl: The Life of Caroline Lockhart.&#8221;</a>  He&#8217;ll be reading and discussing his book <a target="_blank" href="http://30boxes.com/public/134790/JohnClayton/222277348b352a88afd9d393dfbc2c59/1/" title="in many towns across Montana and Wyoming">in many towns across Montana and Wyoming</a> in May and June, beginning with a signing in Greenough, MT tonight, Friday May 18.
</p>
<p>
Tom Miller wrote in about the recent discussion of <a target="_blank" href="http://littourature.blogspot.com/" title="the Kerouac mapping project.">the Kerouac mapping project.</a>  A few years back, Miller edited an anthology of literature of the Mexican border, and created a map to go along with it, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.uapress.arizona.edu/extras/Miller/BorderLitMap.pdf" title="which can be found here">which can be found here</a>.&nbsp; The book, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.uapress.arizona.edu/BOOKS/bid1501.htm" title="Writing on the Edge: Borderlands Literature">Writing on the Edge: Borderlands Literature</a>, is still available from University of Arizona Press.
</p>
<p>
And in Denver, the Lighthouse Writers Workshop is gearing up for its <a target="_blank" href="http://www.lighthousewriters.com/litfest.htm" title="second annual LitFest">second annual LitFest</a> from June 8 to 23, which will feature workshops and discussions with a number of local authors, including Nick Arvin, Laura Pritchett, Brian Kiteley, Janis Hallowell, William Haywood Henderson, and Shari Caudron.
</p>
<p>
Have some more regional literary news or events to share?&nbsp; If so,  <script type="text/javascript">
